//mineral uses Used in Manufacture of glass and ceramics, as an abrasive in sand paper, and in optics to transmit ultraviolet light. Used in construction as limestone and marble to produce cement and concrete. Used in industrial processes such as steel manufacture, as an oxide source and in contrast agents in medical imaging. Used in airplane making industry, electric industry, machinery and civil tool-making industry. It is also used as a desiccating agent, adsorbent, catalyst and in the manufacture of dental cement. Pyrite is used as a gemstone for jewelry production. Some sulfur can be obtained from pyrite as a byproduct of gold production. Monazite is an important source of thorium, cerium, and other rare elements. Exfoliated vermiculite is used in lightweight concrete or plaster, for thermal and acoustic insulation, or as a packing medium, a soil conditioner, as starting medium for seeds, and a filler or extender in paper, paint, or plastics. Used in the manufacture of wallboard, cement, plaster of Paris, soil conditioning, a hardening retarder in Portland cement. Used as a source of magnesia (MgO), a feed additive for livestock, a sintering agent and flux in metal processing, and as an ingredient in the production of glass, bricks, and ceramics. Talc is used a s an ingredient in ceramics, paper, paint, roofing, plastics, cosmetics, talcum and baby powders, and a variety of other assorted uses such as making rubber and plastics. Used in jewelry production. It is also an electrical conductor used in computers, circuits, appliances, cell phones, etc. Natural graphite is used for refractories, batteries, steelmaking, expanded graphite, brake linings, foundry facings and lubricant. Sulfur is a component of gunpowder. It is also used as a component of fertilizers. Used as a gemstone in jewelry production. It is also used as an industrial abrasive as well as other products such as diamond windows, speaker domes, heat sinks, low-friction micro-bearings, etc. Used in winter road treatment, as a source of sodium and chlorine for chemical processes, and for food preservation and seasoning. Hematite is the most important ore of iron. Can also be used for production of pigments, for preparations for heavy media separation, radiation shielding, ballast, etc. Used to plate other metals to protect them against corrosion. Also used in making alloys such as stainless steel. Used in manufacture of refractory products such as bricks, mortars, and kiln furniture used in high temperature furnaces. Used as a precious gem, as an abrasive and for grinding optical glass and polishing metals. Large sheets of mica are mined from pegmatites, these are used to make components for electronic devices, retardation plates, circuit boards, optical filters, detector windows, etc. Used in the manufacturing of paint, joint compound, plastics rubber, asphalt roofing, cosmetics, etc. Used in manufacture of fertilizers, occasional used as a gemstone, as an ore of phosphate to be used in pharmaceuticals, ceramics, silk, textiles, etc. Used in waterjet cutting granules, abrasive blasting granules, filtration granules, abrasive grits and powders, gemstones. Used in metallurgical processes as a slag conditioner. High-magnesium olivine is added to blast furnaces to remove impurities from steel and to form a slag. Used in production of mullite or high-alumina refractories. Used in the manufacture of metals, glass ceramics and cement. Epidote only has minor uses as a gemstone. Chlorite is used as a filler and as a constituent of clay. Ground mica is used as a filler and extender in paints, as an additive to drilling muds, as an inert filler and mold release agent in rubber products, and as a non-stick surface coating on asphalt shingles and rolled roofing. Tourmaline is used as a gemstone and mineral specimen Used in manufacture of refractory ceramic, as a pigment, and for the production of titanium metal. Used as a flux for smelting, and in the production of certain glasses and enamels. Used as an opacifier, whitening agent, and a pigment in glazes and stains used on ceramics and pottery. Used as a substitute for feldspars I the manufacture of glass and ceramics. Used in the production of porcelain. Used in the production of glass and ceramic products. It is also used as ornamental lapidary material with amazonite in green color. Andesine is used as a gemstone. Sometimes cut as a gem when it is clear. Synthetic magnesium cordierite has low thermal expansion and will be used as a semi-refractory material as it is resistant to thermal shock. Tremolite is used to some extent as asbestos material. Titanite is a source of titanium oxide used in pigments. It is also used as a gemstone. Some are used as gemstones but only in rare occurrences when they have an attractive color and clarity. Used in nuclear fuels and nuclear weapons. It is also used in production of high energy X-rays, in photographic toner and as a yellow tint in special glass.
